	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64117623">The discussion on this I've read so far all focuses on using microwaves to downlink power.  That lets the receiver be a "net" of quarter-wave antennas with a diode connection to the main power rail.  It's a big mesh that has plenty of light transmissivity so you can e.g. grow crops or have a park under it.

"Rectenna" is the term for the receivers.</div>
