	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64117601"><p>That sounds really complicated.</p><p>Really really really complicated.</p><p>Sure it's technically possible, but compare to the alternative: putting solar panels right here on earth where they're cheap to transport, easy to install, easy to connect to the grid, and easy to maintain if anything goes wrong.  And when they reach the end of their useful lifespan you take them down, recycle them, and put up new ones.</p><p>They'll also probably last longer on earth where they aren't subject to intense heat from being so close to the sun, ionized particles, and micrometeroid impacts.</p><p>Simple solutions have a lot of advantages over complicated ones.</p></div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_64117601">
