		<div id="comment_body_64119533"><p>Putting them in space is less complicated.  There is a lot of space in space.  And rockets get it there in minutes.</p><p>Also, low Earth orbit is not closer to the sun than the Earth is.  And can be kept well within Earth's magnetic field.</p><p>Another advantage of space-based solar power plants is that they don't have to deal with a day-night cycle.  They can harvest daylight around the clock with no temperature shifts.  So the panels are likely to last a lot longer in space.</p><p>And connecting them to the grid is only a m<span class="substr"> </span></p></div>
	</div>

