		</div>
		<div class="details">
			<span class="by"><span class="byby">by </span><a href="//slashdot.org/~q_e_t">q_e_t</a>  <span class="uid"><a href="//slashdot.org/~q_e_t">( 5104099 )</a></span></a></span><span class="writes" style="display:none"> writes:</span> 
			<span class="otherdetails" id="comment_otherdetails_64117475"></span>
		</div>
	</div>
	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64117475">The earth receives 1.5 billion TWh of insolation per year (340W/m*m average, 510 million km*km). Energy usage (all types) is 160,000TWh.so beaming in all required energy is 160000/1500000000 or an extra 0.01%.</div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_64117475">

