		</div>
	</div>
	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64117609"><p>I think they are right on this one.  It's hard to see the advantage of easier heavy lift and serviceability in LEO being enough to justify the loss of availability.  GEO Orbital solar works at night and is only eclipsed for brief periods per day (around local midnight, averaging 30 minutes) for about a month before and after each equinox.  In LEO your availability goes way down, and you also have larger headaches of drag, pointing and beamforming to a variable distance receiver.</p></div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_64117609">

